1
01:00:00,033 --> 01:00:03,833
<b>On June 16th 2014, a farmer from Virginia</b>

2
01:00:03,833 --> 01:00:06,033
<b>named Jeremiah Heaton planted</b>

3
01:00:06,033 --> 01:00:07,566
<b>a flag in the African desert.</b>

4
01:00:08,400 --> 01:00:10,300
<b>Why? To make his 7 year old</b>

5
01:00:10,300 --> 01:00:11,866
<b>daughter Emily a princess.</b>

6
01:00:12,766 --> 01:00:15,533
<b>He claimed 800 square miles of land</b>

7
01:00:15,533 --> 01:00:18,300
<b>between Egypt and Sudan and called it the</b>

8
01:00:18,300 --> 01:00:19,566
<b>Kingdom of North Sudan.</b>

9
01:00:20,533 --> 01:00:22,933
<b>CNN, Time, Newsweek,</b>

10
01:00:23,666 --> 01:00:25,633
<b>hundreds of outlets covered it.</b>

11
01:00:25,766 --> 01:00:26,900
<b>Most of them treated it like</b>

12
01:00:26,900 --> 01:00:28,566
<b>a cute human interest story.</b>

13
01:00:29,033 --> 01:00:30,166
<b>But here's what almost</b>

14
01:00:30,166 --> 01:00:32,800
<b>nobody explained. He wasn't crazy.</b>

15
01:00:33,366 --> 01:00:35,400
<b>This was one of the only places on earth</b>

16
01:00:35,400 --> 01:00:37,633
<b>besides Antarctica where you could even</b>

17
01:00:37,633 --> 01:00:39,199
<b>try something like this.</b>

18
01:00:39,666 --> 01:00:41,400
<b>Because Berthawil is one of the only</b>

19
01:00:41,400 --> 01:00:42,699
<b>pieces of habitable land</b>

20
01:00:42,699 --> 01:00:44,066
<b>that no country claims.</b>

21
01:00:44,733 --> 01:00:47,633
<b>This isn't a disputed territory, it's not</b>

22
01:00:47,633 --> 01:00:48,900
<b>a border conflict where</b>

23
01:00:48,900 --> 01:00:50,666
<b>both sides claim the same land.</b>

24
01:00:51,366 --> 01:00:53,599
<b>This is the opposite. Both Egypt and</b>

25
01:00:53,599 --> 01:00:55,699
<b>Sudan actively reject it.</b>

26
01:00:56,033 --> 01:00:58,500
<b>And here's the kicker, claiming Berthawil</b>

27
01:00:58,500 --> 01:01:01,000
<b>would cost either Egypt or Sudan the land</b>

28
01:01:01,000 --> 01:01:02,933
<b>that they actually want next door.</b>

29
01:01:03,733 --> 01:01:06,666
<b>Here's why. There's two pieces of land</b>

30
01:01:06,666 --> 01:01:08,000
<b>between Egypt and Sudan.</b>

31
01:01:08,833 --> 01:01:11,533
<b>Berthawil, 800 square miles of landlocked</b>

32
01:01:11,533 --> 01:01:14,233
<b>desert, no water, no infrastructure,</b>

33
01:01:14,966 --> 01:01:15,466
<b>economically</b>

34
01:01:15,466 --> 01:01:17,733
<b>worthless compared to Hala'ip.</b>

35
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:21,866
<b>And the Hala'ip triangle, 800,000 square</b>

36
01:01:21,866 --> 01:01:24,966
<b>miles, 10 times bigger with the Red Sea</b>

37
01:01:24,966 --> 01:01:26,833
<b>coastline and oil potential.</b>

38
01:01:27,566 --> 01:01:28,633
<b>And on top of that,</b>

39
01:01:28,633 --> 01:01:31,166
<b>700,000 tons of manganese.</b>

40
01:01:31,833 --> 01:01:34,366
<b>And here's the problem. Because of how</b>

41
01:01:34,366 --> 01:01:35,333
<b>the British drew the</b>

42
01:01:35,333 --> 01:01:37,500
<b>borders, you can't claim both.</b>

43
01:01:38,300 --> 01:01:41,466
<b>In 1899, Britain and Egypt signed the</b>

44
01:01:41,466 --> 01:01:43,733
<b>Anglo-Egyptian Condominium Agreement.</b>

45
01:01:44,266 --> 01:01:46,533
<b>The treaty says Sudan is defined as</b>

46
01:01:46,533 --> 01:01:47,933
<b>territory south of the</b>

47
01:01:47,933 --> 01:01:50,333
<b>22nd parallel of latitude.</b>

48
01:01:50,699 --> 01:01:53,166
<b>Quite straightforward. A straight line</b>

49
01:01:53,166 --> 01:01:56,033
<b>across the map at the 22nd parallel.</b>

50
01:01:56,400 --> 01:01:59,233
<b>Under this border, Egypt gets Hala'ip and</b>

51
01:01:59,233 --> 01:02:00,833
<b>Sudan gets Berthawil.</b>

52
01:02:01,300 --> 01:02:02,833
<b>But three years later, the British</b>

53
01:02:02,833 --> 01:02:04,166
<b>changed their minds.</b>

54
01:02:04,933 --> 01:02:08,133
<b>On November the 4th in 1902, they created</b>

55
01:02:08,133 --> 01:02:09,733
<b>a new administrative boundary.</b>

56
01:02:10,500 --> 01:02:13,066
<b>Not a straight line this time. This one</b>

57
01:02:13,066 --> 01:02:14,866
<b>was based on tribal use</b>

58
01:02:14,866 --> 01:02:16,300
<b>and settlement patterns.</b>

59
01:02:16,833 --> 01:02:19,933
<b>The Ababdat tribe grazed in Berthawil, so</b>

60
01:02:19,933 --> 01:02:21,066
<b>Britain assigned it to</b>

61
01:02:21,066 --> 01:02:22,266
<b>Egyptian administration.</b>

62
01:02:23,033 --> 01:02:25,533
<b>The Beja tribes in Hala'ip were tied to</b>

63
01:02:25,533 --> 01:02:27,233
<b>Sudan, so they assigned that</b>

64
01:02:27,233 --> 01:02:28,566
<b>to Sudanese administration.</b>

65
01:02:29,633 --> 01:02:32,866
<b>Now, here's the problem. Two borders and</b>

66
01:02:32,866 --> 01:02:35,300
<b>two completely different outcomes.</b>

67
01:02:35,900 --> 01:02:38,766
<b>The 1899 border gives Egypt</b>

68
01:02:38,766 --> 01:02:40,933
<b>Hala'ip the valuable coastline.</b>

69
01:02:41,533 --> 01:02:44,466
<b>The 1902 border gives Sudan the Hala'ip.</b>

70
01:02:44,933 --> 01:02:47,966
<b>Both countries want Hala'ip, so Egypt</b>

71
01:02:47,966 --> 01:02:49,900
<b>claims the 1899 line.</b>

72
01:02:50,466 --> 01:02:53,400
<b>Sudan claims the 1902 line. And</b>

73
01:02:53,400 --> 01:02:56,466
<b>Berthawil? Neither will touch it.</b>

74
01:02:56,733 --> 01:02:58,933
<b>Because claiming Berthawil means</b>

75
01:02:58,933 --> 01:03:00,133
<b>accepting the border</b>

76
01:03:00,133 --> 01:03:01,900
<b>that gives away Hala'ip.</b>

77
01:03:02,133 --> 01:03:03,666
<b>That's why Jeremiah Heaton</b>

78
01:03:03,666 --> 01:03:05,333
<b>could just walk right in.</b>

79
01:03:06,033 --> 01:03:09,433
<b>Two colonial borders. One paradox still</b>

80
01:03:09,433 --> 01:03:12,366
<b>unresolved 70 years after independence.</b>

81
01:03:13,599 --> 01:03:15,133
<b>So why don't they just</b>

82
01:03:15,133 --> 01:03:17,433
<b>negotiate? The Hala'ip triangle.</b>

83
01:03:18,266 --> 01:03:20,633
<b>8,000 square miles. Red Sea coastline</b>

84
01:03:20,633 --> 01:03:23,066
<b>with manganese and possible oil.</b>

85
01:03:23,566 --> 01:03:26,866
<b>In comparison, Berthawil has 800 square</b>

86
01:03:26,866 --> 01:03:28,633
<b>miles of sand and no water.</b>

87
01:03:29,266 --> 01:03:31,633
<b>One is worth fighting for, the other</b>

88
01:03:31,633 --> 01:03:33,300
<b>isn't. Egypt and Sudan</b>

89
01:03:33,300 --> 01:03:34,833
<b>both call it uninhabited.</b>

90
01:03:35,666 --> 01:03:37,366
<b>Tell that to the thousands running</b>

91
01:03:37,366 --> 01:03:38,900
<b>illegal gold mines there,</b>

92
01:03:39,133 --> 01:03:41,633
<b>or the Ababda tribe who've</b>

93
01:03:41,633 --> 01:03:43,133
<b>graced here for generations.</b>

94
01:03:44,066 --> 01:03:46,466
<b>No permanent settlements, no</b>

95
01:03:46,466 --> 01:03:48,400
<b>infrastructure, no government</b>

96
01:03:48,400 --> 01:03:50,699
<b>services, but it's not empty.</b>

97
01:03:51,366 --> 01:03:54,599
<b>And the Ababda? They weren't consulted in</b>

98
01:03:54,599 --> 01:03:57,666
<b>1899. They weren't consulted in 1902.</b>

99
01:03:58,233 --> 01:04:00,433
<b>Their grazing lands just became a</b>

100
01:04:00,433 --> 01:04:02,300
<b>bargaining chip between two governments</b>

101
01:04:02,300 --> 01:04:03,533
<b>that don't want them.</b>

102
01:04:04,033 --> 01:04:04,900
<b>And the dispute over</b>

103
01:04:04,900 --> 01:04:06,766
<b>Hala'ip? It's gotten violent.</b>

104
01:04:07,566 --> 01:04:10,300
<b>In 1992, Sudan granted offshore</b>

105
01:04:10,300 --> 01:04:12,433
<b>exploration rights to a Canadian oil</b>

106
01:04:12,433 --> 01:04:14,566
<b>company. Egypt objected.</b>

107
01:04:15,300 --> 01:04:18,433
<b>In 1994, Egyptian military forces</b>

108
01:04:18,433 --> 01:04:21,000
<b>expelled Sudanese officials from Hala'ip.</b>

109
01:04:21,566 --> 01:04:24,166
<b>In 1995, there was an assassination</b>

110
01:04:24,166 --> 01:04:26,233
<b>attempt on Egyptian President Mubarak.</b>

111
01:04:27,033 --> 01:04:28,966
<b>Egypt blamed Sudan and strengthened</b>

112
01:04:28,966 --> 01:04:30,800
<b>military control over Hala'ip.</b>

113
01:04:31,666 --> 01:04:35,066
<b>By 2000, Sudan withdrew its forces. Egypt</b>

114
01:04:35,066 --> 01:04:37,133
<b>has controlled the territory ever since.</b>

115
01:04:37,866 --> 01:04:39,533
<b>So when Hittin showed up to claim</b>

116
01:04:39,533 --> 01:04:41,800
<b>Berthawil, neither country cared.</b>

117
01:04:42,533 --> 01:04:44,166
<b>His daughter had asked if</b>

118
01:04:44,166 --> 01:04:45,500
<b>she could be a real princess.</b>

119
01:04:45,933 --> 01:04:48,166
<b>In Hittin's own words, "Ain't nothing</b>

120
01:04:48,166 --> 01:04:49,333
<b>more important than my</b>

121
01:04:49,333 --> 01:04:50,133
<b>daughter's happiness,</b>

122
01:04:50,333 --> 01:04:51,566
<b>and now she's got</b>

123
01:04:51,566 --> 01:04:52,933
<b>everything she ever wanted."</b>

124
01:04:53,533 --> 01:04:54,833
<b>He even got permission</b>

125
01:04:54,833 --> 01:04:56,733
<b>from Cairo to make the trip.</b>

126
01:04:57,133 --> 01:04:59,733
<b>Egypt let him drive through, plant his</b>

127
01:04:59,733 --> 01:05:02,433
<b>flag, declare the Kingdom of North Sudan.</b>

128
01:05:03,133 --> 01:05:04,233
<b>Why? Because Egypt</b>

129
01:05:04,233 --> 01:05:05,666
<b>doesn't claim Berthawil.</b>

130
01:05:06,033 --> 01:05:07,266
<b>Letting some American play</b>

131
01:05:07,266 --> 01:05:09,433
<b>pretend costs them nothing.</b>

132
01:05:09,866 --> 01:05:12,833
<b>And he's not alone. Many others have</b>

133
01:05:12,833 --> 01:05:14,466
<b>tried to claim Berthawil.</b>

134
01:05:15,233 --> 01:05:17,966
<b>A Russian radio operator declared it the</b>

135
01:05:17,966 --> 01:05:20,333
<b>Kingdom of Middle-Earth in 2014.</b>

136
01:05:21,133 --> 01:05:22,866
<b>An Indian businessman called</b>

137
01:05:22,866 --> 01:05:25,933
<b>it Kingdom of Dixit in 2017.</b>

138
01:05:26,466 --> 01:05:28,633
<b>Each one with flags, GPS</b>

139
01:05:28,633 --> 01:05:30,466
<b>locks, and bold declarations.</b>

140
01:05:31,800 --> 01:05:33,433
<b>Every claim has been ignored.</b>

141
01:05:33,766 --> 01:05:35,866
<b>The United Nations hasn't recognized any</b>

142
01:05:35,866 --> 01:05:38,133
<b>claimant as Berthawil's legitimate ruler.</b>

143
01:05:38,800 --> 01:05:41,566
<b>Because in modern international law, you</b>

144
01:05:41,566 --> 01:05:42,866
<b>can't just plant a</b>

145
01:05:42,866 --> 01:05:44,266
<b>flag and create a country.</b>

146
01:05:44,666 --> 01:05:47,033
<b>You need a permanent population, a</b>

147
01:05:47,033 --> 01:05:48,433
<b>functioning government, and</b>

148
01:05:48,433 --> 01:05:50,233
<b>recognition from other states.</b>

149
01:05:50,866 --> 01:05:54,300
<b>Berthawil has none of those. So legally,</b>

150
01:05:54,866 --> 01:05:56,333
<b>Emily is not a princess.</b>

151
01:05:57,066 --> 01:05:58,766
<b>But the Hittin story going viral,</b>

152
01:05:59,233 --> 01:06:00,099
<b>millions of views,</b>

153
01:06:00,333 --> 01:06:01,400
<b>hundreds of news outlets,</b>

154
01:06:01,766 --> 01:06:03,566
<b>that reveals something important.</b>

155
01:06:04,133 --> 01:06:07,066
<b>We're fascinated by the idea of unclaimed</b>

156
01:06:07,066 --> 01:06:08,400
<b>land, because almost</b>

157
01:06:08,400 --> 01:06:10,166
<b>none of it exists anymore.</b>

158
01:06:10,933 --> 01:06:13,266
<b>Every piece of habitable land on Earth is</b>

159
01:06:13,266 --> 01:06:14,699
<b>claimed by some country.</b>

160
01:06:15,666 --> 01:06:16,233
<b>Except for...</b>

161
01:06:16,966 --> 01:06:17,866
<b>Berthawil.</b>

162
01:06:18,233 --> 01:06:19,166
<b>Four small pockets</b>

163
01:06:19,166 --> 01:06:20,233
<b>along the Danube River.</b>

164
01:06:20,800 --> 01:06:21,400
<b>But that's a</b>

165
01:06:21,400 --> 01:06:23,566
<b>Croatia-Serbia border dispute.</b>

166
01:06:24,066 --> 01:06:25,000
<b>And parts of Antarctica.</b>

167
01:06:25,599 --> 01:06:28,133
<b>But the Antarctic Treaty System suspends</b>

168
01:06:28,133 --> 01:06:29,166
<b>all of those claims.</b>

169
01:06:29,966 --> 01:06:30,966
<b>That's it.</b>

170
01:06:31,666 --> 01:06:34,366
<b>In a world of 8 billion people divided</b>

171
01:06:34,366 --> 01:06:36,300
<b>into roughly 200 countries.</b>

172
01:06:36,866 --> 01:06:38,033
<b>This is all that's left.</b>

173
01:06:39,266 --> 01:06:41,333
<b>And Berthawil's unclaimed status?</b>

174
01:06:41,800 --> 01:06:42,733
<b>That's a direct result</b>

175
01:06:42,733 --> 01:06:43,800
<b>of European colonialism.</b>

176
01:06:45,033 --> 01:06:47,066
<b>The British drew two borders.</b>

177
01:06:47,733 --> 01:06:49,433
<b>The 1899 line ignored</b>

178
01:06:49,433 --> 01:06:50,933
<b>where tribes actually lived.</b>

179
01:06:51,433 --> 01:06:52,666
<b>It was just a straight line</b>

180
01:06:52,666 --> 01:06:54,033
<b>for political convenience.</b>

181
01:06:54,966 --> 01:06:57,333
<b>The 1902 line tried to fix this by</b>

182
01:06:57,333 --> 01:06:58,833
<b>following tribal territories.</b>

183
01:06:59,433 --> 01:07:01,466
<b>But it created a worse problem.</b>

184
01:07:02,166 --> 01:07:03,766
<b>They drew one border</b>

185
01:07:03,766 --> 01:07:05,066
<b>for political sovereignty,</b>

186
01:07:05,466 --> 01:07:07,033
<b>and then another border for tribal</b>

187
01:07:07,033 --> 01:07:09,266
<b>administration three years later.</b>

188
01:07:09,566 --> 01:07:11,400
<b>They didn't think about what would happen</b>

189
01:07:11,400 --> 01:07:13,633
<b>when Egypt and Sudan became independent.</b>

190
01:07:14,099 --> 01:07:15,300
<b>And the consequences are</b>

191
01:07:15,300 --> 01:07:16,566
<b>still playing out today.</b>

192
01:07:17,666 --> 01:07:20,433
<b>Egypt controls Khalaib by military force.</b>

193
01:07:21,033 --> 01:07:22,866
<b>Sudan still claims it diplomatically.</b>

194
01:07:23,533 --> 01:07:26,866
<b>A 2020 Carnegie Endowment report found</b>

195
01:07:26,866 --> 01:07:29,833
<b>that since Sudan's independence in 1956,</b>

196
01:07:30,633 --> 01:07:32,633
<b>border relations with Egypt have been</b>

197
01:07:32,633 --> 01:07:35,133
<b>characterized more by mutual suspicion</b>

198
01:07:35,266 --> 01:07:36,800
<b>than by peaceful exchange.</b>

199
01:07:37,866 --> 01:07:40,633
<b>And Berthawil is still unclaimed.</b>

200
01:07:41,233 --> 01:07:41,766
<b>Still unwanted.</b>

201
01:07:42,433 --> 01:07:43,699
<b>A colonial leftover</b>

202
01:07:43,699 --> 01:07:45,133
<b>that nobody wants to touch,</b>

203
01:07:45,466 --> 01:07:46,166
<b>because claiming it</b>

204
01:07:46,166 --> 01:07:47,533
<b>means giving up Khalaib.</b>

205
01:07:48,099 --> 01:07:49,433
<b>So when Jeremiah Heaton</b>

206
01:07:49,433 --> 01:07:51,166
<b>planted that flag in 2014,</b>

207
01:07:51,833 --> 01:07:53,333
<b>he wasn't just trying to make his</b>

208
01:07:53,333 --> 01:07:54,166
<b>daughter a princess.</b>

209
01:07:54,866 --> 01:07:56,733
<b>He was highlighting an absurdity.</b>

210
01:07:57,500 --> 01:08:00,099
<b>800 square miles of land between two</b>

211
01:08:00,099 --> 01:08:01,066
<b>countries that</b>

212
01:08:01,066 --> 01:08:02,533
<b>neither country will claim.</b>

213
01:08:03,099 --> 01:08:04,766
<b>Because admitting Berthawil is yours</b>

214
01:08:04,766 --> 01:08:06,966
<b>means admitting Khalaib isn't.</b>

215
01:08:07,433 --> 01:08:08,599
<b>The only land on</b>

216
01:08:08,599 --> 01:08:10,266
<b>earth nobody owns exists,</b>

217
01:08:10,433 --> 01:08:11,599
<b>because two countries are</b>

218
01:08:11,599 --> 01:08:13,266
<b>fighting over the land next door.</b>

219
01:08:14,166 --> 01:08:15,566
<b>And Berthawil isn't unique.</b>

220
01:08:16,166 --> 01:08:18,033
<b>It's just the most visible example.</b>

221
01:08:18,933 --> 01:08:20,399
<b>Across Africa and the Middle East,</b>

222
01:08:20,833 --> 01:08:23,066
<b>colonial borders drawn a century ago</b>

223
01:08:23,133 --> 01:08:25,133
<b>still fuel territorial disputes.</b>

224
01:08:26,133 --> 01:08:26,733
<b>Think about the</b>

225
01:08:26,733 --> 01:08:28,733
<b>Western Sahara, Somaliland,</b>

226
01:08:29,166 --> 01:08:30,333
<b>all those trade lines</b>

227
01:08:30,333 --> 01:08:31,333
<b>cutting through the desert.</b>

228
01:08:32,266 --> 01:08:33,966
<b>The difference? Everyone</b>

229
01:08:33,966 --> 01:08:35,233
<b>wants those territories.</b>

230
01:08:35,966 --> 01:08:37,899
<b>Berthawil is the only one nobody wants.</b>

231
01:08:38,566 --> 01:08:40,266
<b>That's not just a legal curiosity.</b>

232
01:08:40,966 --> 01:08:43,466
<b>That's a colonial border dispute that's</b>

233
01:08:43,466 --> 01:08:44,766
<b>still unresolved 70</b>

234
01:08:44,766 --> 01:08:46,066
<b>years after independence.</b>

235
01:08:46,899 --> 01:08:48,800
